1. Information We Collect
Personal Information You Provide to Us
We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide when you:

Express interest in our products or Services.

Participate in activities on our Services.

Contact us directly.

Examples of personal information we collect include:

Email addresses.

Sensitive Information
We do not process sensitive information.

Social Media Login Data
If you choose to register or log in using a social media account (e.g., Facebook, X), we may receive certain profile information from the social media provider, such as your name, email address, friends list, and profile picture. This information is used only as described in this Privacy Policy.

2. How We Use Your Information
We process your personal information for the following purposes:

To provide, improve, and administer our Services.

To communicate with you, including requesting feedback.

For security and fraud prevention.

To comply with legal obligations.

For other purposes with your consent.

3. Sharing Your Personal Information
We may share your information in the following situations:

Business Transfers: In connection with mergers, sales of company assets, or acquisitions.

Google Maps Platform APIs: To provide location-based services, we may share information with Google Maps APIs, which use GPS, Wi-Fi, and cell towers to estimate your location.

4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to:

Maintain the security of our Services.

Save your preferences.

Assist with basic site functions.

Enable analytics and advertising.

Third parties may also use tracking technologies on our Services for advertising purposes. You can manage your cookie preferences through our Cookie Notice.

5. Social Media Logins
If you register or log in using a social media account, we will receive certain profile information from the provider. We use this information only as described in this Privacy Policy. We are not responsible for how the social media provider uses your information, so please review their privacy policies.

6. Data Retention
We retain your personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law. When no longer needed, we will delete or anonymize your data.

7. Children's Privacy
We do not knowingly collect or market to children under 18. If we learn that we have collected data from a child under 18, we will deactivate the account and delete the information promptly. If you believe we have collected such data, please contact us at [insert email].

8. Your Privacy Rights
Depending on your location, you may have the right to:

Access, update, or delete your personal information.

Withdraw your consent to processing.

Object to certain uses of your data.

To exercise these rights, contact us using the details below.

9. Do-Not-Track Signals
We do not currently respond to Do-Not-Track (DNT) signals from browsers, as no uniform standard has been adopted.

10. Updates to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. The revised version will be posted with an updated "Last Updated" date. Material changes will be communicated to you via email or a prominent notice on our Services.

11. Contact Us
